title: High rate of viral suppression among people new to HIV care

title_detail.value: High rate of viral suppression among people new to HIV care

summary: Eighty-six percent of individuals who entered HIV care soon after diagnosis maintained viral suppression after 48 weeks during a clinical trial. Participants in the clinical trial, called iENGAGE, achieved viral suppression in an average of just 63 days.
